Community


How do we say thanks for the support this area has shown to us?  As often as we can.
At Reserve Oil & Gas, Inc. we’re very proud of the communities and regions we are involved in.  They are full of dedicated people and organizations focused on keeping the local communities strong.  That is why we have been diligent to support local organizations and events whenever possible.  To us, it is one way we are able to say thank you for the trust and confidence the communities have placed in us.
We support the following:

Black Diamond Council of the Girl Scouts of America
Allohak Council of the Boys Scouts of America
University of Charleston Scholarship
West Virginia State University
Roane County High School Engineering Scholarship
Heartwood
The Clay Center
Spencer Black Walnut Festival
Tamarack Foundation
West Virginia University Engineering Scholarship
National Science Foundation
Jackson County Foundation
West Virginia University Athletics Club
Roane County FFA & 4-H Livestock Show & Sale
Mountaineer Challenge Academy


 






